==English==
===Etymology===
An Afrikaans word meaning, literally, "separateness".

===Noun===
'''apartheid'''
#The policy of racial [[separation]] used in South Africa 1948-1990.
*"It has now become an accepted axiom in our dealings with the Natives that it is dishonourable to mix white and black blood... We have felt more and more that if we are to solve our Native question, it is useless to try to govern black and white in the same institutions of government and legislation. They are different not only in colour but in minds and in political capacity." (South African policy is directed at keeping the Native population) “apart as much as possible in our institutions, in land ownership, in forms of government and in many ways….As far as possible, the forms of political government will be satisfied and developed according to his own proper lines.”
'''1917''' General Jan Smuts: Speech at the Savoy Hotel.

2: Policies analogous to the apartheid of South Africa.

